Step 1 — Check the running containers
```
docker ps
```

You should see something like:
```

CONTAINER ID   IMAGE        NAME
...
postgres       researchmind-postgres
```

Step 2 — Connect to the PostgreSQL container

If the container is named researchmind-postgres:
```
docker exec -it researchmind-postgres psql -U researchmind
```

Step 3 — Connect to your database

Inside psql:
```
\l
```
to list databases.

Then:
```
\c researchmind
```


Step 4 — Check the Alembic table
```
SELECT * FROM alembic_version;
```
Step 5 — Clean the migration state (if needed)

If you see the old revision:

f42c5064602a

Since we're still at the beginning of the project, the cleanest fix is:
```
DROP TABLE alembic_version;
```
Then exit:
```
\q
```
